{meta: title Down Where The Dark Waters Flow}
{meta: artist Hank Snow}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Beneath the moon [D7]tonight I [G]kneel
[C]Close to my darling's [G]side
[C]Her eyes in death are forever [G]closed
[D7]My sweet and future [G]bride
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[D7]Sweet wedding bells would softly [G]ring
[C]For us in June she [G]said
[C]But angels thought it best that we [G]part
[D7]And they told us today [G]instead
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[D7]Beside some lonely river [G]bank
[C]Where the weeping willows [G]grow
[C]I'll ease my aching heart [G]tonight
[D7]Down where the dark waters [G]flow
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[D7]I planted on her new made [G]grave
[C]A tender rose with [G]care
[C]To bloom through all of the lonely [G]years
[D7]While she is lying [G]there
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[D7]I'll place one tender kiss of [G]love
[C]Upon that budding [G]rose
[C]And bid my world of cares [G]goodbye
[D7]Down where the dark waters [G]flow
{end_of_verse}

